Oct 26 2007 	Just fab	We spent a night at Millers Residence this week and what a lovely surprise. The hotel is like no other we've ever stayed in and we've stayed in an awful lot. It's tucked away just off the main street with no signage that we could see. The interior is an aladins cave, packed full of art and objects and what can only be called interesting &quot;clutter&quot;. There isn't a surface anywhere with out something on it. The staff were warm and friendly and the host sat and watched TV with us in the evening. There is a complimentary bar where you can help yourself, which was a really nice touch. Our room was lovely and very cosy, I slept fantastically well. Breakfast was around a big table where guests all eat together. I liked it very much, it was a complete contrast to the sterile, ultra modern hotels which are the norm in London. If you like things a bit different and very personal you will love this place.	
